<section class="section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p style="color:var(--muted); font-size:16.5px; max-width:760px;">Every SEO project presents unique technical challenges, search intent patterns, and business goals. Rather than relying on a fixed checklist, I begin by understanding how search engines interpret a website, identifying opportunities for improvement, and developing strategies that align with both user intent and business objectives.</p>
    <p style="color:var(--muted); font-size:16.5px; max-width:760px; margin-top:16px;">My work combines technical SEO, semantic SEO, information architecture, topical authority, and performance analysis to build sustainable organic growth.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section alt">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="eyebrow"><span class="node-dot"></span> METHODOLOGY</div>
      <h2>My SEO Process</h2>
      <p>A structured, seven-stage approach from discovery through continuous improvement.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="process-step">
      <div class="process-num">1</div>
      <div>
        <h3>Business &amp; Website Discovery</h3>
        <p>Every project begins with understanding the business, its services, target audience, competitors, and commercial objectives. This helps ensure SEO recommendations support measurable business outcomes rather than rankings alone.</p>
        <span class="tag blue">Business objectives</span><span class="tag blue">Target audience</span><span class="tag blue">Competitor landscape</span><span class="tag blue">Revenue-driving pages</span><span class="tag blue">Existing performance</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="process-step">
      <div class="process-num">2</div>
      <div>
        <h3>Technical SEO Audit</h3>
        <p>A comprehensive technical audit identifies issues that may prevent search engines from efficiently crawling, rendering, indexing, and understanding the website.</p>
        <span class="tag blue">Crawlability</span><span class="tag blue">Indexability</span><span class="tag blue">Core Web Vitals</span><span class="tag blue">XML Sitemaps</span><span class="tag blue">Robots.txt</span><span class="tag blue">Canonical Tags</span><span class="tag blue">Redirects</span><span class="tag blue">Structured Data</span><span class="tag blue">JavaScript Rendering</span><span class="tag blue">Internal Linking</span><span class="tag blue">Site Architecture</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="process-step">
      <div class="process-num">3</div>
      <div>
        <h3>Search Intent &amp; SERP Analysis</h3>
        <p>Instead of optimizing around keywords alone, I analyze search intent and Google's current search results to understand what users expect and what search engines reward.</p>
        <span class="tag blue">Search intent</span><span class="tag blue">SERP patterns</span><span class="tag blue">Content format</span><span class="tag blue">Entity coverage</span><span class="tag blue">Information gaps</span><span class="tag blue">Competitor analysis</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="process-step">
      <div class="process-num">4</div>
      <div>
        <h3>Semantic SEO Strategy</h3>
        <p>Semantic SEO focuses on building contextual relevance rather than simply increasing keyword usage. Pages are planned around entities, relationships, topical coverage, and user intent to improve how search engines interpret the content.</p>
        <span class="tag blue">Entity identification</span><span class="tag blue">EAV relationships</span><span class="tag blue">Contextual coverage</span><span class="tag blue">Topical maps</span><span class="tag blue">Content clusters</span><span class="tag blue">Representative queries</span><span class="tag blue">Internal knowledge structure</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="process-step">
      <div class="process-num">5</div>
      <div>
        <h3>Content Strategy</h3>
        <p>Content is planned to support the entire customer journey while strengthening topical authority and internal website structure.</p>
        <span class="tag blue">Topical maps</span><span class="tag blue">Content clusters</span><span class="tag blue">Content briefs</span><span class="tag blue">Pillar pages</span><span class="tag blue">Supporting pages</span><span class="tag blue">Service pages</span><span class="tag blue">Location pages</span><span class="tag blue">FAQ strategy</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="process-step">
      <div class="process-num">6</div>
      <div>
        <h3>Implementation</h3>
        <p>Recommendations are implemented across technical SEO, on-page optimization, structured data, internal linking, and content improvements while collaborating with developers, designers, and content teams when required.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="process-step" style="margin-bottom:0;">
      <div class="process-num">7</div>
      <div>
        <h3>Measurement &amp; Continuous Improvement</h3>
        <p>SEO is an ongoing process. Performance is monitored continuously to identify new opportunities, measure progress, and refine strategy.</p>
        <span class="tag blue">Organic traffic</span><span class="tag blue">Keyword visibility</span><span class="tag blue">CTR</span><span class="tag blue">Core Web Vitals</span><span class="tag blue">Index coverage</span><span class="tag blue">Local pack visibility</span><span class="tag blue">Crawl health</span><span class="tag blue">Landing page performance</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
